1
00:01:41,572 --> 00:01:43,449
Get up, get up!

2
00:01:47,812 --> 00:01:49,803
Mixed up in that beating on 12th Street?

3
00:01:49,892 --> 00:01:51,120
No, plain drunkenness.

4
00:01:51,332 --> 00:01:52,811
It says he was picked up there.

5
00:01:52,892 --> 00:01:55,247
They had him on the carpet
down at headquarters.

6
00:01:55,452 --> 00:01:57,363
He's clear. Plain drunkenness.

7
00:01:57,572 --> 00:01:58,527
All right.

8
00:01:59,012 --> 00:01:59,922
Fill it up.

9
00:02:00,012 --> 00:02:01,206
Can I keep it?

10
00:02:01,892 --> 00:02:04,804
Okay. You want to lean him
against something?

11
00:02:05,252 --> 00:02:07,482
- Stand him over there.
- Come on.

12
00:02:24,852 --> 00:02:25,807
Judy?

13
00:02:26,412 --> 00:02:27,845
We're ready for you now.

14
00:02:44,932 --> 00:02:46,365
He must hate me.

15
00:02:46,572 --> 00:02:47,527
What?

16
00:02:49,612 --> 00:02:51,284
He hates me.

17
00:02:52,532 --> 00:02:54,045
What makes you think so?

18
00:02:55,252 --> 00:02:57,402
I don't think. I know.

19
00:02:59,172 --> 00:03:00,605
He looks at me like...

20
00:03:01,172 --> 00:03:03,640
...I was the ugliest thing in the world.

21
00:03:04,692 --> 00:03:06,364
He doesn't like my friends.

22
00:03:06,572 --> 00:03:08,767
He doesn't like one thing about me.

23
00:03:09,452 --> 00:03:11,249
And he called me...

24
00:03:13,572 --> 00:03:15,881
He called me a dirty tramp!

25
00:03:16,932 --> 00:03:18,843
My own father!

26
00:03:20,572 --> 00:03:22,324
Do you think he really means that?

27
00:03:22,572 --> 00:03:23,925
Yes!

28
00:03:24,172 --> 00:03:25,400
No!

29
00:03:26,012 --> 00:03:27,730
I don't know.

30
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:34,562
I mean, maybe he doesn't mean it...

31
00:03:34,772 --> 00:03:36,922
...but he acts like he does.

32
00:03:38,212 --> 00:03:39,804
We were all together.

33
00:03:40,332 --> 00:03:42,846
And we were going to celebrate Easter.

34
00:03:43,892 --> 00:03:46,360
And we were going to catch a double bill.

35
00:03:48,132 --> 00:03:49,406
Big deal!

36
00:03:50,532 --> 00:03:52,602
So I put on my new dress...

37
00:03:53,892 --> 00:03:55,484
...and I came out...

38
00:03:56,452 --> 00:03:58,363
...and he grabbed my face...

39
00:03:59,212 --> 00:04:02,249
...and he started rubbing off all the lipstick.

40
00:04:05,572 --> 00:04:07,802
I thought he'd rub off my lips.

41
00:04:08,932 --> 00:04:11,002
And I ran out of that house.

42
00:04:11,172 --> 00:04:13,732
Is that why you were
wandering around at 1:00 a. m?

43
00:04:17,332 --> 00:04:18,651
Not looking for company?

44
00:04:20,332 --> 00:04:23,005
I don't even know why I do it.

45
00:04:23,492 --> 00:04:25,562
Maybe you get back at your dad that way.

46
00:04:25,652 --> 00:04:28,450
If you're not as close to him
as you'd like to be...

47
00:04:28,852 --> 00:04:31,924
...maybe this is one way
of making him pay attention.

48
00:04:32,132 --> 00:04:33,360
Did you think of that?

49
00:04:34,772 --> 00:04:37,445
I'll never get close to anybody.

50
00:04:38,452 --> 00:04:40,363
Would you go home if we can arrange it?

51
00:04:45,932 --> 00:04:47,684
What's your number, Judy?

52
00:04:48,052 --> 00:04:50,441
We'll ask your dad
to come and pick you up.

53
00:04:50,692 --> 00:04:53,047
Unless you really don't want to go home.

54
00:04:54,452 --> 00:04:56,124
Would you rather stay here?

55
00:05:04,492 --> 00:05:06,847
Lexington 0-5-5-4-9.

56
00:05:22,052 --> 00:05:24,168
That's enough static out of you!

57
00:05:32,172 --> 00:05:34,288
Cut it out now. I'm warning you!

58
00:05:38,012 --> 00:05:40,924
You're shivering, John. Are you cold?

59
00:05:46,172 --> 00:05:47,525
Want my jacket?

60
00:05:54,852 --> 00:05:56,205
Want my jacket?

61
00:05:56,532 --> 00:05:57,885
It's warm.

62
00:06:12,772 --> 00:06:14,410
Your mother will pick you up.

63
00:06:14,692 --> 00:06:15,488
What?

64
00:06:15,812 --> 00:06:17,962
Your mother will be down to pick you up.

65
00:06:18,212 --> 00:06:19,440
My mother!

66
00:06:19,732 --> 00:06:21,324
She's being called for.

67
00:06:22,532 --> 00:06:24,762
You said you'd call my father!

68
00:06:25,572 --> 00:06:27,608
Goodbye, Judy. And take it easy.

69
00:06:28,132 --> 00:06:29,360
Oh, sure!

70
00:06:41,972 --> 00:06:42,882
John Crawford?

71
00:06:42,972 --> 00:06:43,927
Yes, sir?

72
00:06:44,292 --> 00:06:45,725
Come with me, John.

73
00:06:55,132 --> 00:06:56,167
Jim!

74
00:07:04,092 --> 00:07:05,445
Happy Easter.

75
00:07:06,292 --> 00:07:07,645
Happy Easter.

76
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:09,690
Where were you tonight?

77
00:07:09,892 --> 00:07:12,247
They called us,
and I got the fright of my life!

78
00:07:12,332 --> 00:07:14,288
Where were you tonight, Jimbo?

79
00:07:23,812 --> 00:07:25,643
Well, then, there now.

80
00:07:26,732 --> 00:07:28,768
Were you having a ball, Dad?

81
00:07:31,012 --> 00:07:33,401
Well, everybody's been having a ball.

82
00:07:37,412 --> 00:07:39,528
You're the king of the ball, Dad.

83
00:07:47,212 --> 00:07:48,964
You think I'm funny?

84
00:08:03,132 --> 00:08:05,168
Why didn't you take my jacket?

85
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,046
Jim Stark?

86
00:08:16,692 --> 00:08:17,647
John.

87
00:08:19,732 --> 00:08:20,687
John!

88
00:08:23,812 --> 00:08:26,485
Do you have any idea
why you shot those puppies?

89
00:08:27,972 --> 00:08:30,691
Is that what they call you,
or do you have a nickname?

90
00:08:31,652 --> 00:08:32,448
Plato.

91
00:08:32,652 --> 00:08:34,529
He was a Greek philosopher.

92
00:08:35,572 --> 00:08:39,247
You talk nice to the man now, hear?
He's going to help you.

93
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:42,325
Nobody can help me.

94
00:08:42,612 --> 00:08:44,921
Can you tell me why
you killed those puppies?

95
00:08:46,452 --> 00:08:47,601
No, sir.

96
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,603
Where'd you get the gun?

97
00:08:53,092 --> 00:08:54,286
My mother's drawer.

98
00:08:55,052 --> 00:08:57,043
Where's your mother tonight, Plato?

99
00:08:57,812 --> 00:08:58,688
She's away.

100
00:08:58,932 --> 00:09:01,048
She's always going away somewhere.

101
00:09:01,252 --> 00:09:04,449
She's got a sister in Chicago,
and she's there for the holiday.

102
00:09:04,892 --> 00:09:06,041
Where's your father?

103
00:09:06,132 --> 00:09:07,804
They're not together, sir.

104
00:09:08,212 --> 00:09:10,680
We haven't seen him now in a long time.

105
00:09:11,852 --> 00:09:13,251
Do you ever hear from him?

106
00:09:13,452 --> 00:09:16,808
I don't think it's right for a mother
to go and leave her child.

107
00:09:17,012 --> 00:09:18,889
It's his birthday today, sir.

108
00:09:20,972 --> 00:09:23,167
Did the boy ever talk to a psychiatrist?

109
00:09:24,932 --> 00:09:26,411
You mean a head shrinker?

110
00:09:27,252 --> 00:09:29,720
Mrs. Crawford don't believe in them, sir.

111
00:09:30,572 --> 00:09:32,369
Maybe she'd better start.

112
00:09:32,612 --> 00:09:34,648
Sit over there for just a minute, please.

113
00:09:40,532 --> 00:09:43,808
I don't see what's so bad
about taking a little drink.

114
00:09:43,972 --> 00:09:45,405
You don't?

115
00:09:45,652 --> 00:09:46,687
He's a minor...

116
00:09:46,852 --> 00:09:49,525
...and it looks like he had more
than a "little drink."

117
00:09:50,372 --> 00:09:51,725
Don't hum, dear.

118
00:09:52,172 --> 00:09:54,891
I cut loose pretty good in my day too.

119
00:09:55,092 --> 00:09:56,127
Really, Frank?

120
00:09:56,572 --> 00:09:57,527
When was that?

121
00:09:57,612 --> 00:09:59,568
Can't you wait till we get home?

122
00:09:59,772 --> 00:10:00,761
How about you?

123
00:10:01,012 --> 00:10:02,809
Got anything to say for yourself?

124
00:10:04,092 --> 00:10:05,366
Not interested?

125
00:10:05,892 --> 00:10:07,484
Can't you answer?

126
00:10:07,692 --> 00:10:09,045
What's the matter with you?

127
00:10:09,132 --> 00:10:10,724
He's just loaded, honey.

128
00:10:10,932 --> 00:10:12,968
I was talking to Jim!

129
00:10:13,252 --> 00:10:17,006
Well, I'd like to just explain.
You see, we just moved here...

130
00:10:17,212 --> 00:10:19,772
...and the kid hasn't got any friends.

131
00:10:19,972 --> 00:10:21,405
Tell him why we moved here.

132
00:10:21,572 --> 00:10:22,800
Will you hold it?

133
00:10:23,012 --> 00:10:24,445
Tell the man why we moved.

134
00:10:24,612 --> 00:10:26,682
- Will you hold it!
- You can't protect me.

135
00:10:27,012 --> 00:10:31,244
Do you mind if I try? Do you
have to slam the door in my face?

136
00:10:31,852 --> 00:10:34,764
I try to get to him. What happens?

137
00:10:34,972 --> 00:10:37,964
I buy you everything you want.
A bicycle? You get it!

138
00:10:38,172 --> 00:10:40,208
- A car...
- You buy me many things.

139
00:10:40,412 --> 00:10:42,448
Not just buying!

140
00:10:42,652 --> 00:10:44,643
We give you love and affection, don't we?

141
00:10:44,732 --> 00:10:46,006
Then what is it?

142
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:48,089
Was it because we went to that party?

143
00:10:48,292 --> 00:10:52,126
You know what kind of drunken brawls
those kind of parties turn into.

144
00:10:52,532 --> 00:10:53,681
It's no place for kids!

145
00:10:53,772 --> 00:10:56,366
A minute ago,
you said you didn't care if he drinks.

146
00:10:56,572 --> 00:10:58,369
He said a "little" drink.

147
00:10:58,772 --> 00:11:01,570
You're tearing me apart!

148
00:11:03,012 --> 00:11:06,846
You say one thing, he says another,
and everybody changes back again!

149
00:11:07,612 --> 00:11:09,011
That's a fine way to behave!

150
00:11:09,092 --> 00:11:11,481
Well, you know who he takes after.

151
00:11:17,612 --> 00:11:18,965
Inside, Jim.

152
00:11:20,612 --> 00:11:21,442
Come on.

153
00:11:21,892 --> 00:11:22,847
Inside.

154
00:11:24,172 --> 00:11:26,288
- Excuse us a minute.
- Yeah, sure.

155
00:11:32,172 --> 00:11:35,005
Somebody ought to put poison
in her Epsom salts.

156
00:11:35,572 --> 00:11:36,607
Grandma?

157
00:11:37,572 --> 00:11:38,846
Get lost.

158
00:11:39,332 --> 00:11:41,721
Hang loose, boy. I'm warning you.

159
00:11:44,372 --> 00:11:46,442
Why don't you wash up and go home?

160
00:11:47,012 --> 00:11:48,445
This is cute.

161
00:11:49,332 --> 00:11:51,323
Big, tough character!

162
00:11:51,852 --> 00:11:53,729
You don't kid me, pal.

163
00:11:54,292 --> 00:11:56,408
How come you're not wearing your boots?

164
00:11:58,212 --> 00:11:59,611
Well, that's cute.

165
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,161
That's cute.

166
00:12:17,092 --> 00:12:19,003
It's too bad you didn't connect.

167
00:12:20,572 --> 00:12:22,688
You could have gone to juvenile hall.

168
00:12:24,132 --> 00:12:25,724
That's what you want, isn't it?

169
00:12:28,172 --> 00:12:29,446
Sure, it is.

170
00:12:31,612 --> 00:12:34,046
You want to bug us
till we have to lock you up.

171
00:12:34,692 --> 00:12:35,522
Why?

172
00:12:35,732 --> 00:12:37,290
- Leave me alone.
- No.

173
00:12:39,332 --> 00:12:40,401
I don't know why.

174
00:12:40,492 --> 00:12:42,130
Go on, don't give me that!

175
00:12:42,532 --> 00:12:46,366
Please, lock me up. I'll hit somebody.
I'll do something, and I don't...

176
00:12:48,852 --> 00:12:49,921
Try the desk.

177
00:12:53,892 --> 00:12:54,847
Go ahead.

178
00:13:30,972 --> 00:13:33,725
Is that why you moved?
You were in trouble?

179
00:13:35,172 --> 00:13:36,525
No, they think...

180
00:13:38,412 --> 00:13:41,563
...that they can protect me
by moving around all the time.

181
00:13:42,172 --> 00:13:45,687
You had a good start in the wrong
direction. Why'd you do it?

182
00:13:47,292 --> 00:13:48,441
What do you mean?

183
00:13:49,412 --> 00:13:50,891
Mess a kid up?

184
00:13:55,972 --> 00:13:57,246
He called me chicken.

185
00:13:58,732 --> 00:14:00,370
Your folks didn't understand?

186
00:14:02,492 --> 00:14:03,845
They never do.

187
00:14:08,692 --> 00:14:11,001
They think that I can make friends...

188
00:14:12,132 --> 00:14:13,087
...if we move.

189
00:14:17,412 --> 00:14:20,643
Just move. Everything
will be roses and sunshine.

190
00:14:21,092 --> 00:14:23,322
But you don't think
that's the right solution?

191
00:14:26,812 --> 00:14:29,372
She eats him alive and he takes it.

192
00:14:29,732 --> 00:14:31,643
Things pretty rough for you at home?

193
00:14:33,252 --> 00:14:34,367
That's a zoo!

194
00:14:34,852 --> 00:14:35,807
What?

195
00:14:37,372 --> 00:14:38,691
That's a zoo!

196
00:14:41,092 --> 00:14:43,686
I mean, he always wants to be my pal,
you know?

197
00:14:45,452 --> 00:14:48,171
But how can I give him anything if he's...

198
00:14:50,812 --> 00:14:54,487
I mean, I love him and all that type of stuff.

199
00:14:56,372 --> 00:14:58,090
I don't want to hurt him.

200
00:14:58,692 --> 00:15:02,002
But then I don't know what to do anymore.

201
00:15:02,212 --> 00:15:04,407
Except maybe die.

202
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:08,287
If he had guts to knock Mom cold once...

203
00:15:08,532 --> 00:15:11,649
...then maybe she'd be happy
and she'd stop picking on him.

204
00:15:12,332 --> 00:15:14,721
Because they make mush out of him!

205
00:15:15,492 --> 00:15:18,245
You know, just mush!

206
00:15:21,412 --> 00:15:24,768
I'll tell you one thing,
I don't ever want to be like him.

207
00:15:25,652 --> 00:15:26,448
Chicken?

208
00:15:27,452 --> 00:15:29,761
I'll bet you see right through me,
don't you?

209
00:15:34,092 --> 00:15:36,925
How can a guy grow up
in a circus like that?

210
00:15:37,252 --> 00:15:38,685
Beats me, Jim.

211
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:41,166
But they do.

212
00:15:41,532 --> 00:15:42,760
Want some water?

213
00:15:48,932 --> 00:15:51,162
If I had one day...

214
00:15:56,132 --> 00:15:58,600
...when I didn't have to be all confused...

215
00:16:00,372 --> 00:16:03,842
...and I didn't have to feel
that I was ashamed of everything...

216
00:16:04,772 --> 00:16:06,922
If I felt that I belonged someplace...

217
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:08,884
You know? Then...

218
00:16:14,612 --> 00:16:16,443
Will you do something for me?

219
00:16:19,052 --> 00:16:23,284
If the pot starts boiling again,
will you see me before you get in a jam?

220
00:16:24,292 --> 00:16:27,284
If you want to talk,
come in and shoot the breeze.

221
00:16:28,052 --> 00:16:30,520
It's easier sometimes
than talking to your folks.

222
00:16:35,172 --> 00:16:37,003
Anytime, night or day.

223
00:16:44,132 --> 00:16:47,886
You calmed down enough
to go back in there now?

224
00:16:50,332 --> 00:16:51,970
Are you serious?

225
00:16:59,492 --> 00:17:00,766
Mother, I'm sorry.

226
00:17:00,932 --> 00:17:02,729
It's all right, darling.

227
00:17:03,092 --> 00:17:04,286
Mister Officer...

228
00:17:04,572 --> 00:17:06,528
...this was all very unfortunate.

229
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:10,367
He made a mistake, and he's sorry,
so we won't have any more trouble.

230
00:17:10,812 --> 00:17:12,962
He was always a lovely boy.

231
00:17:13,172 --> 00:17:16,608
Grandmother, you tell one more lie
and you'll turn to stone.

232
00:17:20,052 --> 00:17:21,007
Look, Jim...

233
00:17:21,212 --> 00:17:22,361
...don't forget.

234
00:17:23,132 --> 00:17:25,202
Have some cigars?

235
00:17:25,972 --> 00:17:27,405
No, thanks. I don't smoke.

236
00:17:27,612 --> 00:17:28,965
Give them to your friends.

237
00:17:29,052 --> 00:17:30,371
No, thanks, Mr. Stark.

238
00:17:30,452 --> 00:17:32,443
Frank, he doesn't want any.

239
00:17:39,172 --> 00:17:41,891
Jim, your eggs are on the table, dear.

240
00:17:46,172 --> 00:17:47,890
Sit down. Eat. You'll be late.

241
00:17:48,772 --> 00:17:49,727
Beau!

242
00:17:54,972 --> 00:17:56,405
Come here, Beau!

243
00:17:58,092 --> 00:17:59,491
Beau, come on!

244
00:18:00,332 --> 00:18:02,482
I don't think I want anything.

245
00:18:03,892 --> 00:18:04,847
I'm nervous.

246
00:18:05,092 --> 00:18:07,731
My first day of school,
Mother made me eat so much...

247
00:18:07,932 --> 00:18:09,650
...I couldn't swallow until recess.

248
00:18:10,092 --> 00:18:11,605
Did you fix any sandwiches?

249
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:14,043
There's meatloaf and peanut butter...

250
00:18:17,412 --> 00:18:19,642
What did I tell you? Peanut butter.

251
00:18:22,052 --> 00:18:23,849
There's a thermos of orange juice...

252
00:18:24,052 --> 00:18:26,122
...and some applesauce cake to go with it.

253
00:18:26,332 --> 00:18:27,606
And I baked it.

254
00:18:33,532 --> 00:18:34,521
Goodbye, Mom.

255
00:18:34,732 --> 00:18:38,407
Young fellow, you knock them dead
like your old man used to.

256
00:18:39,732 --> 00:18:41,245
You know what I think?

257
00:18:41,452 --> 00:18:43,886
I feel maybe we'll stay here awhile.

258
00:18:44,452 --> 00:18:47,171
Listen, watch out
about choosing your pals.

259
00:18:47,372 --> 00:18:48,771
Don't let them choose you.

260
00:19:03,652 --> 00:19:04,607
Wait a minute.

261
00:19:14,772 --> 00:19:16,046
I've seen you before.

262
00:19:16,292 --> 00:19:19,011
- Stop the world!
- You don't have to be unfriendly.

263
00:19:19,172 --> 00:19:20,764
Well, now that's true.

264
00:19:21,292 --> 00:19:23,248
But life is crushing in on me.

265
00:19:23,452 --> 00:19:25,602
Life can be beautiful.

266
00:19:29,012 --> 00:19:31,685
- I know where it was.
- Where what was?

267
00:19:33,212 --> 00:19:34,770
Where I first saw you.

268
00:19:36,332 --> 00:19:38,323
Everything going okay now?

269
00:19:40,212 --> 00:19:41,645
