No, you give me a direct answer!

535
00:42:13,772 --> 00:42:15,808
Are you going to keep me from going?

536
00:42:16,372 --> 00:42:18,328
Did I ever stop you from anything?

537
00:42:19,012 --> 00:42:20,445
You're at a wonderful age.

538
00:42:20,532 --> 00:42:23,444
In ten years, you'll look back
on this and wish...

539
00:42:23,652 --> 00:42:25,051
Ten years?

540
00:42:26,532 --> 00:42:29,000
I want an answer now. I need one.

541
00:42:29,892 --> 00:42:34,204
Listen, Jimbo, I'm just trying
to show you how foolish you are.

542
00:42:34,412 --> 00:42:37,324
When you're older,
you'll look back at this...

543
00:42:37,532 --> 00:42:39,488
...and you'll laugh at yourself...

544
00:42:39,652 --> 00:42:42,689
...for thinking that this is so important.

545
00:42:43,332 --> 00:42:45,243
It's not as if you were alone.

546
00:42:45,452 --> 00:42:48,046
This has happened to every boy.

547
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:52,645
It happened to me when I was your age,
maybe a year older.

548
00:42:56,972 --> 00:42:58,200
What's all the excitement?

549
00:42:58,292 --> 00:43:00,886
I've been working hard
getting this house in order...

550
00:43:00,972 --> 00:43:02,371
Jim had blood on him.

551
00:43:02,572 --> 00:43:05,370
- He just ran out.
- And you didn't stop him?

552
00:43:54,372 --> 00:43:55,930
Hey, Chicken Little!

553
00:43:56,132 --> 00:43:58,202
Where's toreador? He beg off?

554
00:43:58,372 --> 00:44:00,408
He's not scared of you.

555
00:44:04,052 --> 00:44:06,247
- There he is.
- Over there, man.

556
00:44:11,132 --> 00:44:13,600
- How did you get here?
- I hitched.

557
00:44:14,772 --> 00:44:17,525
I bet you'd go to a hanging, wouldn't you?

558
00:44:17,732 --> 00:44:20,200
I guess it's just my morbid personality.

559
00:44:22,052 --> 00:44:23,041
Should I leave?

560
00:44:23,132 --> 00:44:24,406
No, it's okay.

561
00:44:39,932 --> 00:44:42,162
Come on. Let's go see what we're driving.

562
00:44:52,172 --> 00:44:53,730
No, just him.

563
00:44:53,932 --> 00:44:55,729
It's okay. Stay here.

564
00:44:58,452 --> 00:45:00,329
What did you say your name was?

565
00:45:01,412 --> 00:45:02,731
Jim Stark.

566
00:45:02,932 --> 00:45:05,287
Yeah, I'm Buzz Gunderson.

567
00:45:08,132 --> 00:45:09,884
I got some goodies for you.

568
00:45:10,052 --> 00:45:11,644
You got a flashlight?

569
00:45:16,132 --> 00:45:17,804
Is he a friend of yours?

570
00:45:22,252 --> 00:45:24,083
Yeah, he's my best friend.

571
00:45:25,532 --> 00:45:26,851
What's he like?

572
00:45:29,892 --> 00:45:31,405
I don't know.

573
00:45:32,012 --> 00:45:33,570
You have to get to know him.

574
00:45:34,532 --> 00:45:35,885
He doesn't say much.

575
00:45:36,092 --> 00:45:38,208
But when he does, you know he means it.

576
00:45:38,492 --> 00:45:39,891
He's sincere.

577
00:45:40,932 --> 00:45:42,604
Well, that's the main thing.

578
00:45:42,852 --> 00:45:45,082
- You want to flip?
- Yeah, go ahead.

579
00:45:48,092 --> 00:45:49,207
Heads.

580
00:45:51,812 --> 00:45:55,566
Maybe next summer, he'll take me
hunting with him. And fishing.

581
00:45:56,372 --> 00:46:00,047
I want him to teach me because
I know he won't get mad if I goof.

582
00:46:01,092 --> 00:46:02,366
His name's Jim.

583
00:46:02,572 --> 00:46:05,644
It's really James, but he likes Jim more.

584
00:46:07,012 --> 00:46:10,243
And people he really likes,
he lets them call him Jamie.

585
00:46:10,932 --> 00:46:12,081
Jamie?

586
00:46:13,412 --> 00:46:14,765
Try the doors.

587
00:46:18,052 --> 00:46:19,804
Hey, try it with the jump.

588
00:46:45,892 --> 00:46:47,450
That's the edge.

589
00:46:48,892 --> 00:46:49,881
That's the end.

590
00:46:53,892 --> 00:46:55,325
Certainly is.

591
00:46:58,972 --> 00:47:00,405
You know something?

592
00:47:02,892 --> 00:47:04,371
I like you.

593
00:47:05,732 --> 00:47:07,051
You know that?

594
00:47:08,812 --> 00:47:10,211
Why do we do this?

595
00:47:10,412 --> 00:47:12,448
You got to do something...

596
00:47:12,772 --> 00:47:14,125
...now, don't you?

597
00:47:48,692 --> 00:47:50,489
Take them up all the way to the end.

598
00:47:50,692 --> 00:47:52,045
Get all the girls!

599
00:47:52,892 --> 00:47:54,564
Bring it up to the left side.

600
00:47:58,972 --> 00:48:00,803
Crunch, line them up!

601
00:48:01,332 --> 00:48:04,130
Go to the end and
bring your cars up on the right.

602
00:48:04,292 --> 00:48:06,442
Put your car on the left-hand side.

603
00:48:06,652 --> 00:48:08,847
Turn your lights in toward the center.

604
00:48:09,052 --> 00:48:10,371
Let's line them up!

605
00:48:10,532 --> 00:48:11,965
Moose, come here.

606
00:48:12,132 --> 00:48:15,329
Straighten them out.
Tell them when to turn on their lights.

607
00:48:15,492 --> 00:48:16,891
Johnny!

608
00:48:17,092 --> 00:48:19,526
Follow that dark roadster over there.

609
00:48:30,452 --> 00:48:31,328
You're okay?

610
00:48:31,492 --> 00:48:32,766
Give me some dirt.

611
00:48:41,252 --> 00:48:42,605
Hey, toreador!

612
00:48:44,892 --> 00:48:46,041
She signals...

613
00:48:46,212 --> 00:48:48,043
...we head for the edge.

614
00:48:48,572 --> 00:48:50,688
And the first man who jumps is a chicken.

615
00:48:51,172 --> 00:48:52,446
All right?

616
00:49:13,732 --> 00:49:14,960
Me too.

617
00:49:17,412 --> 00:49:19,767
May I have some dirt, please?

618
00:49:58,412 --> 00:50:00,289
Hit your lights!

619
00:51:31,132 --> 00:51:32,042
Where's Buzz?

620
00:51:32,132 --> 00:51:33,565
Down there.

621
00:51:39,532 --> 00:51:40,931
Let's get out of here!

622
00:51:48,052 --> 00:51:49,041
Down there.

623
00:51:49,252 --> 00:51:51,049
Down there is Buzz!

624
00:52:53,572 --> 00:52:55,005
This is fine.

625
00:53:05,892 --> 00:53:07,291
You'll be all right?

626
00:53:20,772 --> 00:53:22,330
You want to see a monkey?

627
00:53:55,332 --> 00:53:58,244
Want to come home with me?
There's nobody at my house.

628
00:53:58,452 --> 00:54:00,522
Heck, I'm not tired. Are you?

629
00:54:00,732 --> 00:54:03,007
I don't have too many people I can talk to.

630
00:54:03,212 --> 00:54:04,565
Who has?

631
00:54:05,092 --> 00:54:06,969
If you want to come, we could talk...

632
00:54:07,172 --> 00:54:09,811
...then we could have breakfast,
like my dad used to.

633
00:54:09,892 --> 00:54:11,644
If only you could've been my dad...

634
00:54:11,732 --> 00:54:13,085
You flipped or something?

635
00:54:13,292 --> 00:54:14,361
Look.

636
00:54:16,292 --> 00:54:18,601
I'll see you in the morning, okay?

637
00:54:18,932 --> 00:54:21,526
I've got to pick up my scooter anyway,
you know.

638
00:54:21,732 --> 00:54:22,926
I know.

639
00:54:28,052 --> 00:54:29,405
See you tomorrow.

640
00:54:56,412 --> 00:54:58,562
Hello, little cute sister.

641
00:54:59,812 --> 00:55:03,646
Hello, darling, baby-pie,
glamour puss, sweetie.

642
00:55:08,612 --> 00:55:10,204
You belong in bed.

643
00:56:50,692 --> 00:56:52,125
He's home!

644
00:56:52,412 --> 00:56:53,891
You're home!

645
00:57:00,412 --> 00:57:01,401
You're home.

646
00:57:01,572 --> 00:57:03,210
Are you all right?

647
00:57:03,412 --> 00:57:05,289
Where were you? We were so worried.

648
00:57:06,892 --> 00:57:09,247
I wouldn't take a sleeping pill
till you were home.

649
00:57:09,332 --> 00:57:12,130
Can I talk to you guys?
I have to talk to somebody.

650
00:57:17,412 --> 00:57:19,801
You better give me an answer this time.

651
00:57:19,972 --> 00:57:21,405
Go ahead.

652
00:57:21,692 --> 00:57:23,569
A direct answer.

653
00:57:24,612 --> 00:57:26,204
I'm in trouble.

654
00:57:26,452 --> 00:57:29,046
You know that big,
high bluff near Millertown?

655
00:57:29,252 --> 00:57:31,049
Yes, there was a bad accident there.

656
00:57:31,252 --> 00:57:34,289
They showed the pictures on television.

657
00:57:35,172 --> 00:57:36,127
I was in it.

658
00:57:36,212 --> 00:57:37,167
How can you...

659
00:57:37,372 --> 00:57:39,840
It doesn't matter how.
I was driving a stolen car.

660
00:57:39,932 --> 00:57:43,720
That's a fine thing! Do you enjoy
doing this to me, or what?

661
00:57:43,932 --> 00:57:46,730
- You wanted him to make a list!
- Let him tell it!

662
00:57:46,932 --> 00:57:48,411
She doesn't care!

663
00:57:48,612 --> 00:57:51,809
You remember how I almost died
giving birth to him?

664
00:57:52,012 --> 00:57:55,084
- And then you say I don't care!
- Please relax, relax!

665
00:58:00,132 --> 00:58:01,167
Dad...

666
00:58:02,132 --> 00:58:04,930
...I said it was a matter of honor.

667
00:58:05,412 --> 00:58:06,447
Remember?

668
00:58:09,412 --> 00:58:11,164
They called me chicken.

669
00:58:12,772 --> 00:58:15,161
You know? Chicken?

670
00:58:19,492 --> 00:58:20,971
I had to go.

671
00:58:30,252 --> 00:58:33,403
If I didn't, I'd never be able
to face those kids again.

672
00:58:38,212 --> 00:58:40,328
I got in one of those cars...

673
00:58:40,812 --> 00:58:43,929
...and Buzz, one of those kids,
he got in the other car...

674
00:58:44,132 --> 00:58:46,362
...and we had to drive fast...

675
00:58:46,692 --> 00:58:49,331
...and then jump before the car
came to the edge.

676
00:58:49,532 --> 00:58:51,966
And I got out okay and Buzz didn't.

677
00:58:54,772 --> 00:58:56,444
And it killed him.

678
00:58:56,612 --> 00:58:58,523
I can't keep it to myself anymore.

679
00:58:58,692 --> 00:59:00,489
You just get it off your chest.

680
00:59:00,692 --> 00:59:03,206
That is not what I mean!

681
00:59:04,932 --> 00:59:07,400
I have never done anything right.

682
00:59:07,612 --> 00:59:10,843
I've been going around with
my head in a sling for years.

683
00:59:11,492 --> 00:59:14,723
I don't want to drag you into this,
but I can't help it.

684
00:59:14,932 --> 00:59:16,365
You see, I think...

685
00:59:17,572 --> 00:59:22,202
...you can't just go around proving
things and pretending like you're tough.

686
00:59:22,412 --> 00:59:23,367
That's right.

687
00:59:23,572 --> 00:59:26,530
And even though you got to
look a certain way...

688
00:59:26,732 --> 00:59:29,246
- You're absolutely right!
- You look, you feel...

689
00:59:29,452 --> 00:59:31,647
You're not listening to me!

690
00:59:32,132 --> 00:59:34,771
You're involved in this, just like I am!

691
00:59:35,932 --> 00:59:39,004
I'm going to the police
and telling them I'm involved.

692
00:59:39,172 --> 00:59:40,321
Did anyone see you?

693
00:59:40,532 --> 00:59:43,285
- Did anyone see your license plate?
- I don't know!

694
00:59:43,492 --> 00:59:45,528
Will the others go to the police?

695
00:59:45,732 --> 00:59:47,643
It doesn't matter. It doesn't matter.

696
00:59:47,852 --> 00:59:50,764
- Why be the only one involved?
- Far be it from me...

697
00:59:50,972 --> 00:59:53,532
Do we have to listen to a sermon now?

698
00:59:53,732 --> 00:59:55,529
I'm telling him what you mean.

699
00:59:55,732 --> 00:59:59,088
You can't be idealistic all your life.
Nobody thanks you for...

700
00:59:59,292 --> 01:00:02,204
- Except to yourself!
- Wait a minute!

701
01:00:02,372 --> 01:00:03,964
Except yourself.

702
01:00:05,572 --> 01:00:06,846
You don't want me to go?

703
01:00:08,012 --> 01:00:10,207
No, I don't want you to go to the police.

704
01:00:10,372 --> 01:00:12,761
Why should you be the only one involved?

705
01:00:12,972 --> 01:00:16,647
But I am involved! We are all involved!

706
01:00:18,212 --> 01:00:21,409
A boy, a kid was killed tonight!

707
01:00:22,092 --> 01:00:24,811
I can't get out of it and
pretend it didn't happen!

708
01:00:25,012 --> 01:00:27,970
Well, you know
that you did the wrong thing.

709
01:00:28,132 --> 01:00:30,487
- That's the main thing.
- That's nothing.

710
01:00:30,692 --> 01:00:33,331
That is absolutely nothing. Dad, you said...

711
01:00:33,532 --> 01:00:36,683
...you want me to tell the truth.
Didn't you say that?

712
01:00:40,852 --> 01:00:42,331
You can't turn it off.

713
01:00:42,532 --> 01:00:46,161
He's not saying that.
He's saying just don't volunteer!

714
01:00:46,932 --> 01:00:48,604
Just tell a little white lie.

715
01:00:48,772 --> 01:00:51,605
You'll learn! When you're older, Jim.

716
01:00:52,332 --> 01:00:55,449
Well, I don't think
that I want to learn that way.

717
01:00:55,652 --> 01:00:58,291
It doesn't matter anyway,
because we're moving!

718
01:00:58,932 --> 01:01:00,285
Don't tear me loose again.

719
01:01:00,452 --> 01:01:03,012
- Just why are we moving?
- Must I spell it out?

720
01:01:03,172 --> 01:01:05,811
- You won't use me as an excuse again!
- I don't!

721
01:01:06,012 --> 01:01:08,128
When you can't face yourself
you blame me!

722
01:01:08,292 --> 01:01:09,691
That is not true!

723
01:01:10,492 --> 01:01:12,926
You say it's because of me
or the neighborhood!

724
01:01:13,092 --> 01:01:15,686
You use every other phony excuse!

725
01:01:16,292 --> 01:01:19,443
Mom, I just...
Once, I want to do something right!

726
01:01:19,652 --> 01:01:22,485
And I don't want you
to run away from me again!

727
01:01:25,652 --> 01:01:29,167
- This is all going too fast.
- You better give me something.

728
01:01:29,372 --> 01:01:31,442
You better give me something fast.

729
01:01:31,652 --> 01:01:33,210
Jimmy, you're very young.

730
01:01:33,412 --> 01:01:35,972
A foolish decision now
could wreck your whole life!

731
01:01:36,172 --> 01:01:39,323
- In ten years you won't know it happened.
- Dad, answer her.

732
01:01:41,052 --> 01:01:42,246
Tell her.

733
01:01:43,892 --> 01:01:45,405
Ten years.

734
01:01:47,612 --> 01:01:49,762
Dad, let me hear you answer her.

735
01:02:03,292 --> 01:02:05,123
Dad, stand up for me.

736
01:02:15,652 --> 01:02:17,085
Stand up!

737
01:02:19,012 --> 01:02:20,127
You'll kill him!

738
01:02:22,852 --> 01:02:24,046
You're killing him!

739
01:02:24,492 --> 01:02:26,210
You want to kill your own father?

740
01:03:02,812 --> 01:03:05,884
- See how they brought us in like that?
- Let go of me!

741
01:03:06,092 --> 01:03:08,162
You want a good crack in the mouth?

742
01:03:08,372 --> 01:03:10,567
Take it easy, Ed. The boy's on edge.

743
01:03:10,812 --> 01:03:13,201
- Come on.
- He shouldn't talk to me that way.

744
01:03:13,412 --> 01:03:15,368
After all, I am his father.

745
01:03:15,932 --> 01:03:18,287
This place appeal to you or something?

746
01:03:26,132 --> 01:03:28,362
- What's he going to pull?
- Nothing, Crunch.

747
01:03:28,572 --> 01:03:31,769
- Did you see any cops with him?
- He was pulled in like us.

748
01:03:32,172 --> 01:03:35,323
Hey, excuse me.
Can you tell me where I can find...

749
01:03:36,332 --> 01:03:38,721
I forgot his name.
He works in the juvenile...

750
01:03:38,932 --> 01:03:40,126
Can't you see I'm writing?

751
01:03:42,190 --> 01:03:44,306
He's going to tell, man. I know.

752
01:03:45,310 --> 01:03:46,902
Nobody arrested him.

753
01:03:47,510 --> 01:03:48,829
I think I better go home.

754
01:03:49,030 --> 01:03:50,588
Hey, wait, man.

755
01:03:51,390 --> 01:03:53,108
We'll have some kicks, huh?

756
01:03:54,870 --> 01:03:57,623
- Crunch, my father...
- We'll bring him down.

757
01:03:57,830 --> 01:03:59,149
What do you say?

758
01:04:05,150 --> 01:04:06,742
You're going to clobber him?

759
01:04:08,630 --> 01:04:10,905
What, are you out of your mind? Come on.

760
01:04:12,070 --> 01:04:15,062
- What I could write about you...
- I remember his name.

761
01:04:15,230 --> 01:04:16,982
- What's the charge?
- Assault.

762
01:04:17,150 --> 01:04:20,506
- His name is Ray. I'd like to see him.
- He's not here.

763
01:04:20,710 --> 01:04:22,143
He's not in Juvenile Hall.

764
01:04:22,350 --> 01:04:25,308
I don't know where he is.
He'll be out all night.

765
01:04:25,470 --> 01:04:26,505
How old are you?

766
01:04:26,950 --> 01:04:29,703
My parents know I'm here.
They know I'm out here.

767
01:04:30,510 --> 01:04:32,660
Come back in the morning, will you?

768
01:04:32,870 --> 01:04:34,383
Well, can I wait?

769
01:04:35,230 --> 01:04:37,107
Have you ever been booked before?

770
01:04:37,590 --> 01:04:39,069
Solid.

771
01:05:06,590 --> 01:05:07,625
Hello?

772
01:05:08,150 --> 01:05:09,378
Who wants her?

773
01:05:10,150 --> 01:05:11,105
Who?

774
01:05:11,750 --> 01:05:13,149
Jim who?

775
01:05:13,790 --> 01:05:15,223
I never heard of you!

776
01:05:17,990 --> 01:05:20,265
He didn't have to hang up on him.

777
01:05:51,910 --> 01:05:53,263
Hello, Jamie.

778
01:05:54,510 --> 01:05:55,625
Jamie?

779
01:06:04,470 --> 01:06:06,222
Where'd you get that?

780
01:06:11,550 --> 01:06:13,461
How long have you known Plato?

781
01:06:18,030 --> 01:06:19,065
About...

782
01:06:20,750 --> 01:06:23,025
<i>- Coming up, another request.</i>
...this morning.

783
01:06:23,230 --> 01:06:26,267
<i>This time, from the boys</i>
<i>at Anna's Pizza Paradise.</i>

784
01:06:26,430 --> 01:06:29,308
<i>A new arrangement</i>
<i>of an oldie in rhythm and blues.</i>

785
01:06:29,550 --> 01:06:31,700
<i>Jim, this is dedicated to you...</i>

786
01:06:32,150 --> 01:06:33,424
<i>... from Buzz.</i>

787
01:06:50,750 --> 01:06:52,422
They'll be looking for you.

788
01:06:55,270 --> 01:06:57,625
I didn't chicken. You saw where I jumped.

789
01:06:57,790 --> 01:06:59,781
What do I have to do, kill myself?

790
01:07:00,830 --> 01:07:03,025
It doesn't matter to them.

791
01:07:04,470 --> 01:07:07,223
Well, I guess you're still pretty upset, huh?

792
01:07:09,230 --> 01:07:10,788
I'm just numb.

793
01:07:18,390 --> 01:07:19,789
You know something?

794
01:07:22,110 --> 01:07:24,340
I woke up this morning, you know?

795
01:07:26,470 --> 01:07:28,347
And the sun was shining...

796
01:07:28,870 --> 01:07:30,622
...and it was nice...

797
01:07:31,150 --> 01:07:32,981
...and all that type of stuff.

798
01:07:33,470 --> 01:07:36,303
And the first thing, I saw you.

799
01:07:39,430 --> 01:07:40,499
And I said:

800
01:07:40,790 --> 01:07:44,465
"This will be one terrific day,
so you better live it up...

801
01:07:44,670 --> 01:07:47,980
"...because tomorrow you'll be nothing."

802
01:07:48,990 --> 01:07:50,503
See? And I almost was.

803
01:07:52,350 --> 01:07:53,749
I'm sorry.

804
01:07:55,230 --> 01:07:57,790
I'm sorry that I treated you mean today.

805
01:07:59,070 --> 01:08:02,426
Don't believe what I say
when I'm with the rest of the kids.

806
01:08:03,350 --> 01:08:06,069
Nobody acts sincere.

807
01:08:18,630 --> 01:08:20,029
Why did you do that?

808
01:08:20,190 --> 01:08:21,782
I felt like it.

809
01:08:25,270 --> 01:08:26,988
Your lips are soft.

810
01:08:36,350 --> 01:08:37,465
Where are you going?

811
01:08:37,550 --> 01:08:38,903
I don't know.

812
01:08:43,270 --> 01:08:44,828
We can't stay here.

813
01:08:55,110 --> 01:08:56,748
I know one thing.

814
01:08:58,590 --> 01:09:01,946
- I'm not going back in that zoo.
- I'm never going back!

815
01:09:09,070 --> 01:09:10,264
Listen...

816
01:09:13,270 --> 01:09:16,103
I know a place. Plato told me before.

817
01:09:16,310 --> 01:09:18,187
It's an old, deserted mansion...

818
01:09:18,590 --> 01:09:20,342
...up by the planetarium.

819
01:09:21,790 --> 01:09:23,382
Want to go up there with me?

820
01:09:32,030 --> 01:09:33,463
You can trust me, Judy.

821
01:09:40,070 --> 01:09:42,061
Okay.

822
01:09:57,350 --> 01:09:59,341
- What do you want?
- Your friend!

823
01:09:59,550 --> 01:10:01,700
Yeah, we got eyes for him. You know it?

824
01:10:02,670 --> 01:10:05,662
- Where does he live?
- You guys better beat it!

825
01:10:05,870 --> 01:10:07,383
Where does he live?

826
01:10:07,590 --> 01:10:08,943
Tell us! Tell us!

827
01:10:09,150 --> 01:10:11,300
- Leave me alone!
- Where does he live?

828
01:10:12,630 --> 01:10:13,858
Get him! Come on!

829
01:10:18,150 --> 01:10:19,344
We want your friend!

830
01:10:21,150 --> 01:10:23,220
I got it! I got his address book!

831
01:10:23,430 --> 01:10:24,909
Your friend talked!

832
01:10:25,110 --> 01:10:26,145
Now you talk!

833
01:10:26,350 --> 01:10:27,942
Talk! Talk!

834
01:10:28,830 --> 01:10:30,582
What are you doing to him?

835
01:10:32,390 --> 01:10:34,540
Let's get out of here!

836
01:10:35,550 --> 01:10:37,461
- Did you get the book?
- Got it!

837
01:11:00,030 --> 01:11:03,181
Why you want to mix up with
bad boys like that?

838
01:11:03,390 --> 01:11:06,109
Why you want to get into trouble
all the time?

839
01:11:07,630 --> 01:11:10,428
What you doing with that?
You put that down!

840
01:11:10,590 --> 01:11:12,945
Put it down before you hurt yourself!

841
01:11:13,150 --> 01:11:14,469
I have to warn him!

842
01:11:17,510 --> 01:11:19,307
You stay home, John!

843
01:11:22,110 --> 01:11:23,702
Bill Sibley.

844
01:11:26,230 --> 01:11:27,868
Sam Stuart.

845
01:11:28,550 --> 01:11:30,347
Stark. Jim Stark. Here it is.

846
01:11:30,550 --> 01:11:33,622
1<i>7</i>53 Angelo. Well, well!

847
01:11:40,670 --> 01:11:42,023
Frank, I'm frightened!

848
01:11:42,230 --> 01:11:44,505
- What's that pounding?
- I don't know.

849
01:11:44,670 --> 01:11:47,503
At first I thought it was Jim...
He's not home yet.

850
01:11:47,710 --> 01:11:50,224
He's home, dear. I heard his car.

851
01:11:50,630 --> 01:11:54,464
- Well, are you going down there?
- Look, will you please relax?

852
01:11:55,550 --> 01:11:56,824
Now, you see?

853
01:11:57,350 --> 01:11:58,578
It stopped.

854
01:12:00,510 --> 01:12:02,740
I still think you ought to go down there.

855
01:12:17,830 --> 01:12:19,183
Who's there?

856
01:12:20,670 --> 01:12:22,262
Anybody there?

857
01:12:24,190 --> 01:12:25,305
Open it.

858
01:12:36,910 --> 01:12:38,468
Who's out there?

859
01:12:39,790 --> 01:12:42,588
- Where's your son?
- Where's your baby boy gone to?

860
01:12:42,750 --> 01:12:45,310
- We want to talk to him.
- He's not here.

861
01:12:49,710 --> 01:12:51,223
Look in his room!

862
01:12:58,590 --> 01:12:59,545
Son?

863
01:13:09,190 --> 01:13:10,100
Is he there?

864
01:13:10,310 --> 01:13:12,221
No, honey, he's not here.

865
01:13:21,430 --> 01:13:23,898
- What are you doing?
- Do you know where Jim is?

866
01:13:24,030 --> 01:13:25,782
No, I don't know.

867
01:13:25,990 --> 01:13:27,708
Do you know where he is?

868
01:13:30,350 --> 01:13:31,544
I think...

869
01:13:35,910 --> 01:13:37,662
I'm sorry I bothered you.

870
01:13:37,870 --> 01:13:39,383
Hey, come back here!

871
01:13:39,550 --> 01:13:40,778
Who are you?

872
01:14:16,590 --> 01:14:18,023
Careful, Jim.

873
01:14:36,190 --> 01:14:38,101
Those noisy neighbors.

874
01:14:40,550 --> 01:14:41,505
Come on!

875
01:14:45,470 --> 01:14:46,585
Jim, it's me.

876
01:14:56,030 --> 01:14:57,782
They're looking for you.

877
01:14:58,510 --> 01:15:00,740
Everybody.
Crunch and Goon and everybody!

878
01:15:00,950 --> 01:15:01,939
We know.

879
01:15:02,830 --> 01:15:05,025
They think you told the police on them.

880
01:15:05,390 --> 01:15:06,584
They're going to...

881
01:15:10,750 --> 01:15:12,024
Who's in there?

882
01:15:12,190 --> 01:15:14,624
Nobody. Just us chickens.

883
01:15:17,390 --> 01:15:18,345
Who's in there?

884
01:15:18,550 --> 01:15:20,506
Judy. Judy's up there.

885
01:15:22,350 --> 01:15:24,500
- Let me in?
- Yeah. All right.

886
01:15:24,670 --> 01:15:26,581
But your house is a mess.

887
01:15:30,590 --> 01:15:31,864
Watch out.

888
01:15:34,990 --> 01:15:37,299
- Where'd he go?
- I don't know.

889
01:15:48,990 --> 01:15:50,662
Well, we're safe here.

890
01:15:51,270 --> 01:15:52,339
I hope.

891
01:15:57,270 --> 01:15:59,147
What do you think of my castle?

892
01:16:04,430 --> 01:16:05,863
Well, now, there, then...

893
01:16:06,070 --> 01:16:08,300
I think we'll take it for the summer.

894
01:16:08,590 --> 01:16:10,103
Right this way.

895
01:16:13,310 --> 01:16:14,948
Would you like to rent it?

896
01:16:15,150 --> 01:16:18,267
Or are you more in the mood to buy, dear?

897
01:16:19,110 --> 01:16:20,941
You decide, darling.

898
01:16:21,390 --> 01:16:24,143
- Remember our budget.
- Don't give it a thought.

899
01:16:24,350 --> 01:16:27,069
It's only $3,000,000 a month.

900
01:16:29,230 --> 01:16:30,424
We can manage that.

901
01:16:30,510 --> 01:16:33,786
I'll scrimp and save
and work my fingers to the bone.

902
01:16:33,990 --> 01:16:35,981
You see, we're newlyweds.

903
01:16:36,950 --> 01:16:38,542
Oh, there's just one thing.

904
01:16:38,750 --> 01:16:40,024
What about?

905
01:16:41,310 --> 01:16:42,584
Children?

906
01:16:44,150 --> 01:16:45,947
Right this way.

907
01:16:46,750 --> 01:16:47,705
Yes.

908
01:16:48,190 --> 01:16:50,420
We really don't encourage them.

909
01:16:50,750 --> 01:16:52,706
They're so noisy and troublesome.

910
01:16:52,910 --> 01:16:54,343
Don't you agree?

911
01:16:54,870 --> 01:16:56,622
And so annoying when they cry.

912
01:16:56,830 --> 01:16:59,822
I don't know what to do when they cry.
Do you, dear?

913
01:17:00,030 --> 01:17:01,622
Drown them like puppies!

914
01:17:02,430 --> 01:17:05,308
The nursery's far away
from the rest of the house.

915
01:17:05,470 --> 01:17:06,823
Forgot to wind your sundial.

916
01:17:06,910 --> 01:17:10,869
If you have children,
you'll find this is a wonderful arrangement.

917
01:17:12,190 --> 01:17:14,226
They can carry on and you won't notice.

918
01:17:14,430 --> 01:17:16,102
A sunken nursery!

919
01:17:16,510 --> 01:17:20,469
In fact, if you lock them in,
you'll never have to see them again.

920
01:17:20,670 --> 01:17:22,661
- Much less, talk to them.
- Talk to them?

921
01:17:22,870 --> 01:17:26,067
- Nobody talks to children.
- No, they just tell them.

922
01:17:28,990 --> 01:17:30,309
What time is it?

923
01:17:31,230 --> 01:17:33,027
Hang loose. We've got all night.

924
01:17:33,430 --> 01:17:36,979
I wonder if the maid could tell
who we were if she saw us again.

925
01:17:37,150 --> 01:17:38,344
Sure she could.

926
01:17:38,990 --> 01:17:40,059
I know she could.

927
01:17:40,350 --> 01:17:42,147
You still want to go home, Moose?

928
01:17:43,790 --> 01:17:45,428
Then shut your mouth...

929
01:17:45,670 --> 01:17:47,547
...before your guts run out.

930
01:17:50,110 --> 01:17:51,702
Quick, fill the pool!

931
01:17:56,990 --> 01:17:58,946
Let's see how long we can stay under.

932
01:18:00,830 --> 01:18:02,786
You can't talk underwater.

933
01:18:24,670 --> 01:18:26,467
I never saw you having so much fun.

934
01:18:26,670 --> 01:18:29,662
I came here a lot of times before,
but I never had fun.

935
01:18:29,870 --> 01:18:31,144
Why not?

936
01:18:31,750 --> 01:18:33,263
Because I was alone.

937
01:18:37,870 --> 01:18:39,462
All right!

938
01:18:41,390 --> 01:18:43,028
What'd you come back here for?

939
01:18:43,230 --> 01:18:46,063
Because I'd run away.
I used to run away a lot...

940
01:18:46,270 --> 01:18:47,862
...but they always took me back.

941
01:18:47,950 --> 01:18:48,905
Who?

942
01:18:49,310 --> 01:18:50,663
Mom and Dad.

943
01:18:52,030 --> 01:18:54,225
Now that I don't have them I wish...

944
01:18:54,910 --> 01:18:56,662
...I never had run away.

945
01:18:57,990 --> 01:19:00,026
I used to lie in my crib at night...

946
01:19:00,630 --> 01:19:02,382
...and I'd listen to them fight.

947
01:19:02,990 --> 01:19:04,981
Can you remember back that far?

948
01:19:06,550 --> 01:19:09,781
I can't even remember
what happened yesterday.

949
01:19:11,350 --> 01:19:12,669
I can't.

950
01:19:13,630 --> 01:19:14,506
How do you do it?

951
01:19:14,590 --> 01:19:17,309
I went to a head shrinker.
He made me remember.

952
01:19:17,510 --> 01:19:18,306
Did he?

953
01:19:18,510 --> 01:19:22,549
Then my mother said it cost too much,
so she went to Hawaii instead.

954
01:19:24,790 --> 01:19:26,508
Well, what's your problem?

955
01:19:26,910 --> 01:19:28,343
I don't know...

956
01:19:29,630 --> 01:19:30,983
...but I'm happy now.

957
01:19:31,630 --> 01:19:32,745
Here.

958
01:19:33,470 --> 01:19:35,620
I wish we could stay here.

959
01:19:38,710 --> 01:19:40,302
Where's your father now?

960
01:19:42,670 --> 01:19:43,864
He's dead.

961
01:19:45,030 --> 01:19:47,225
He was a hero in the China Sea.

962
01:19:50,470 --> 01:19:52,825
You told me he was
a big wheel in New York.

963
01:19:55,550 --> 01:19:56,778
I did?

964
01:19:58,030 --> 01:19:59,861
What's the difference?

965
01:20:00,630 --> 01:20:02,461
He might as well be dead anyway.

966
01:20:03,750 --> 01:20:05,468
It's all right.

967
01:20:07,510 --> 01:20:10,183
Sure. Sure.

968
01:20:20,590 --> 01:20:22,626
I wonder how many rooms in this place?

969
01:20:23,510 --> 01:20:26,070
I don't know. A lot, probably.

970
01:20:26,550 --> 01:20:27,869
Probably.

971
01:20:32,510 --> 01:20:34,262
Do you want to explore?

972
01:21:14,470 --> 01:21:16,700
Must have been a nervous day.

973
01:21:17,150 --> 01:21:19,220
He must have started out nervous.

974
01:21:20,670 --> 01:21:22,706
I've done that, though. Haven't you?

975
01:21:58,190 --> 01:22:00,306
That looks like our boy's car, huh?

976
01:22:00,670 --> 01:22:02,467
Well, what do you know?

977
01:22:18,270 --> 01:22:20,704
Is this what it's like to love somebody?

978
01:22:21,070 --> 01:22:22,389
I don't know.

979
01:22:24,350 --> 01:22:27,148
What kind of a person
do you think a girl wants?

980
01:22:29,670 --> 01:22:30,580
A man.

981
01:22:33,630 --> 01:22:36,986
But a man who can be gentle and sweet.

982
01:22:37,870 --> 01:22:39,269
Like you are.

983
01:22:42,790 --> 01:22:45,782
And someone who doesn't
run away when you want them.

984
01:22:46,830 --> 01:22:50,061
Like being Plato's friend
when nobody else liked him.

985
01:22:51,190 --> 01:22:53,146
That's being strong.

986
01:23:03,950 --> 01:23:06,259
We're not going to be lonely anymore.

987
01:23:07,190 --> 01:23:08,942
Ever, ever.

988
01:23:09,790 --> 01:23:11,587
Not you or me.

989
01:23:12,990 --> 01:23:15,220
I love somebody.

990
01:23:16,070 --> 01:23:17,822
All the time I've been...

991
01:23:18,190 --> 01:23:20,340
...looking for someone to love me.

992
01:23:21,470 --> 01:23:23,381
And now I love somebody.

993
01:23:24,950 --> 01:23:26,781
And it's so easy.

994
01:23:28,630 --> 01:23:30,348
Why is it easy now?

995
01:23:33,190 --> 01:23:34,509
I don't know.

996
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:37,142
It is for me too.

997
01:23:38,910 --> 01:23:40,582
I love you, Jim.

998
01:23:41,350 --> 01:23:43,261
I really mean it.

999
01:23:46,430 --> 01:23:48,341
Well, I'm glad.

1000
01:24:23,190 --> 01:24:24,339
Good morning.

1001
01:24:39,070 --> 01:24:40,344
Let's take him!

1002
01:26:47,390 --> 01:26:48,300
That's it.

1003
01:26:48,990 --> 01:26:50,548
This is unit 1<i>7.</i>

1004
