1060
01:32:46,430 --> 01:32:48,546
There are some other kids in trouble.

1061
01:32:49,030 --> 01:32:50,463
You'll have to go with me.

1062
01:32:50,550 --> 01:32:52,984
Sure, sure. That's all right.

1063
01:32:58,230 --> 01:32:59,982
Lieutenant says seal them off.

1064
01:33:18,070 --> 01:33:19,389
Hello, Ray.

1065
01:33:19,750 --> 01:33:21,229
You know anything about this?

1066
01:33:21,310 --> 01:33:22,504
No more than you do.

1067
01:33:22,590 --> 01:33:24,342
A kid's in there with a gun.

1068
01:33:24,510 --> 01:33:27,627
He wounded another kid
and shot at an officer.

1069
01:33:28,350 --> 01:33:31,069
- You got a speaker?
- Yeah, help yourself.

1070
01:33:34,270 --> 01:33:37,228
- What's going on?
- Some kid's in trouble. Stay back.

1071
01:33:37,430 --> 01:33:40,502
I got to know! My boy ran off
and he got a gun too.

1072
01:33:40,710 --> 01:33:42,428
All right. Lieutenant!

1073
01:33:43,150 --> 01:33:45,425
<i>I'm addressing the boy in the planetarium.</i>

1074
01:33:45,630 --> 01:33:47,382
<i>I'm speaking to the boy inside.</i>

1075
01:33:48,150 --> 01:33:50,869
<i>This is Ray Frameck</i>
<i>from the Juvenile Division.</i>

1076
01:33:51,630 --> 01:33:53,586
<i>Armed police are outside.</i>

1077
01:33:54,030 --> 01:33:57,705
<i>Whoever you are,</i>
<i>drop your weapon and come out.</i>

1078
01:33:59,310 --> 01:34:00,823
<i>Come outside!</i>

1079
01:34:01,350 --> 01:34:05,628
<i>Clasp your hands over your head</i>
<i>and come outside quietly.</i>

1080
01:34:08,150 --> 01:34:09,105
Mr. Stark!

1081
01:34:09,470 --> 01:34:10,823
Frank!

1082
01:34:14,030 --> 01:34:15,463
That's my son.

1083
01:34:18,510 --> 01:34:19,579
Hold your fire!

1084
01:34:23,510 --> 01:34:24,704
Are you sure?

1085
01:34:25,070 --> 01:34:26,662
I think I know my son.

1086
01:34:30,710 --> 01:34:34,623
<i>Officers, another boy and girl</i>
<i>just ran into the planetarium.</i>

1087
01:34:34,830 --> 01:34:36,548
<i>We don't know if they're armed.</i>

1088
01:34:36,750 --> 01:34:39,742
<i>Hold your positions</i>
<i>until further instructions.</i>

1089
01:34:40,350 --> 01:34:43,581
<i>Another boy and girl just ran</i>
<i>into the planetarium.</i>

1090
01:34:43,790 --> 01:34:45,701
<i>We don't know if they're armed.</i>

1091
01:34:45,950 --> 01:34:49,181
<i>Hold your positions</i>
<i>until further instructions.</i>

1092
01:34:50,870 --> 01:34:52,098
You in there?

1093
01:34:53,030 --> 01:34:55,225
You're my friend, Plato.

1094
01:34:56,310 --> 01:34:58,062
That means a lot to me.

1095
01:34:58,670 --> 01:35:01,389
Hey! I'm going to open the door now.

1096
01:35:12,110 --> 01:35:13,987
You can shoot me if you want to.

1097
01:35:21,630 --> 01:35:24,224
Boy, I'm blind as a bat.

1098
01:35:24,470 --> 01:35:25,949
You got a match?

1099
01:35:29,070 --> 01:35:30,708
I'll break my neck in here.

1100
01:35:30,790 --> 01:35:32,189
Where are you?

1101
01:35:33,470 --> 01:35:34,983
I've got a gun.

1102
01:35:37,950 --> 01:35:39,269
Yeah, I know.

1103
01:35:42,830 --> 01:35:45,298
- Light a match, will you?
- No.

1104
01:35:48,470 --> 01:35:49,698
How are you?

1105
01:35:50,910 --> 01:35:52,423
I'm fine.

1106
01:35:52,630 --> 01:35:54,109
That's fine.

1107
01:36:02,910 --> 01:36:06,585
Do you think the end of the world
will come at nighttime?

1108
01:36:10,550 --> 01:36:11,869
At dawn.

1109
01:36:15,150 --> 01:36:16,822
Come on, now.

1110
01:36:19,350 --> 01:36:20,669
Where are you?

1111
01:36:27,710 --> 01:36:29,063
What are you hiding for?

1112
01:36:29,270 --> 01:36:30,703
Just stand up.

1113
01:36:31,550 --> 01:36:34,110
How can I talk to you if I can't see you?

1114
01:36:35,390 --> 01:36:37,620
I can't talk to you if I can't see you.

1115
01:36:38,750 --> 01:36:40,308
Come on, stand up.

1116
01:36:40,990 --> 01:36:44,062
You've seen this show before. Come on.

1117
01:36:45,950 --> 01:36:47,747
Do you see that star up there?

1118
01:36:49,670 --> 01:36:50,989
Stand up. Look at it.

1119
01:36:53,070 --> 01:36:55,265
I can't talk to you if I can't see you.

1120
01:36:55,470 --> 01:36:56,903
That's all there is to it.

1121
01:37:07,710 --> 01:37:10,429
I'm not going to hurt you
or anything like that.

1122
01:37:17,670 --> 01:37:19,706
Why did you run out on me?

1123
01:37:21,790 --> 01:37:23,462
We didn't run out on you.

1124
01:37:24,310 --> 01:37:26,301
We were coming right back, I told you.

1125
01:37:26,510 --> 01:37:27,909
You sure?

1126
01:37:28,950 --> 01:37:30,702
Sure, I'm sure.

1127
01:37:32,550 --> 01:37:33,903
Judy's here.

1128
01:37:34,710 --> 01:37:36,746
She's waiting. Come on.

1129
01:37:37,990 --> 01:37:38,900
Come on.

1130
01:37:42,110 --> 01:37:44,101
No? Not ready to come out yet?

1131
01:37:52,510 --> 01:37:54,580
Promise you, nothing will happen.

1132
01:37:57,870 --> 01:37:59,223
Are you cold?

1133
01:38:00,070 --> 01:38:01,025
Here.

1134
01:38:04,350 --> 01:38:06,022
It's warm. Here.

1135
01:38:06,910 --> 01:38:08,787
My jacket. It's warm.

1136
01:38:10,710 --> 01:38:12,143
Can I keep it?

1137
01:38:12,350 --> 01:38:13,942
Well, what do you think?

1138
01:38:18,950 --> 01:38:21,464
Hey, now can I have the gun, Plato?

1139
01:38:21,630 --> 01:38:23,222
You want to give it to me?

1140
01:38:25,150 --> 01:38:27,300
- My gun?
- Yeah. In your pocket.

1141
01:38:27,510 --> 01:38:28,784
Give it to me.

1142
01:38:38,430 --> 01:38:40,022
No, I need it.

1143
01:38:44,030 --> 01:38:45,941
Don't you trust me, Plato?

1144
01:38:48,150 --> 01:38:49,788
Just give it to me for a second.

1145
01:38:59,070 --> 01:39:01,265
Been carrying this around all day?

1146
01:39:09,150 --> 01:39:10,549
Now there's a...

1147
01:39:12,470 --> 01:39:14,267
...lot of people out front.

1148
01:39:16,670 --> 01:39:18,547
You promised to give it back.

1149
01:39:20,430 --> 01:39:22,580
Friends always keep their promises.

1150
01:39:27,150 --> 01:39:28,583
These people...

1151
01:39:30,270 --> 01:39:34,229
You know, every one
of them want to see that you're safe.

1152
01:39:34,510 --> 01:39:36,148
You understand that?

1153
01:39:36,670 --> 01:39:38,388
They want you to be safe.

1154
01:39:40,510 --> 01:39:42,228
And... Oh, here.

1155
01:39:42,670 --> 01:39:44,626
They said I could come in here...

1156
01:39:44,830 --> 01:39:46,707
...and I could bring you out, and...

1157
01:39:46,910 --> 01:39:47,945
Why?

1158
01:39:49,590 --> 01:39:50,705
Why?

1159
01:39:51,710 --> 01:39:53,223
Because they like you.

1160
01:39:57,310 --> 01:39:58,425
Come on.

1161
01:40:15,870 --> 01:40:17,303
It's too bright.

1162
01:40:22,510 --> 01:40:23,829
I'll fix it.

1163
01:40:36,990 --> 01:40:39,379
Is Ray Frameck still out there?

1164
01:40:40,710 --> 01:40:41,859
<i>Yes, I'm here.</i>

1165
01:40:43,430 --> 01:40:45,466
Hey, turn out those lights!

1166
01:40:45,950 --> 01:40:47,702
If you do, we'll come out!

1167
01:40:48,830 --> 01:40:50,263
<i>Turn your lights out.</i>

1168
01:40:58,270 --> 01:41:00,022
See? Come on.

1169
01:41:11,150 --> 01:41:11,980
Who's that?

1170
01:41:13,310 --> 01:41:15,346
- Just a guy.
- I shot at one of them.

1171
01:41:15,550 --> 01:41:17,586
It's all right. You didn't hurt him.

1172
01:41:17,790 --> 01:41:19,621
Those are not my friends!

1173
01:41:20,430 --> 01:41:22,102
Make them go away.

1174
01:41:24,510 --> 01:41:28,628
You want me to make them go away?
You want me to fix it? Okay.

1175
01:41:33,950 --> 01:41:36,418
Ray, can you make those guys get back?

1176
01:41:36,630 --> 01:41:39,303
You don't have to worry
about anything. Here.

1177
01:41:39,510 --> 01:41:41,068
Keep the guys back.

1178
01:41:42,190 --> 01:41:44,181
That other kid still has a gun.

1179
01:41:48,030 --> 01:41:50,260
Don't turn on the lights! It's too bright.

1180
01:41:50,430 --> 01:41:52,944
Plato doesn't... Turn out the lights!

1181
01:42:05,470 --> 01:42:07,347
I got the bullets!

1182
01:42:07,990 --> 01:42:09,469
Look!

1183
01:42:13,830 --> 01:42:14,819
Let him alone!

1184
01:42:15,030 --> 01:42:17,225
Who are you? What do you want?

1185
01:42:17,430 --> 01:42:19,785
All right, fellas. All right, Lieutenant.

1186
01:42:22,470 --> 01:42:23,983
Get the stretcher in here.

1187
01:42:24,390 --> 01:42:25,789
For a minute there, I...

1188
01:42:26,390 --> 01:42:28,506
When I saw that red jacket, I...

1189
01:42:28,710 --> 01:42:29,904
I thought...

1190
01:42:39,750 --> 01:42:41,502
Hey, jerkpot...

1191
01:42:43,110 --> 01:42:44,748
...what'd you do that for?

1192
01:42:52,550 --> 01:42:54,268
You can't help it, son.

1193
01:42:54,750 --> 01:42:57,025
You did everything a man could.

1194
01:43:20,550 --> 01:43:22,268
Help me.

1195
01:43:25,550 --> 01:43:27,461
You can depend on me.

1196
01:43:27,670 --> 01:43:29,183
Trust me.

1197
01:43:30,430 --> 01:43:33,547
Whatever comes, we'll face it together.

1198
01:43:33,870 --> 01:43:35,303
I swear it.

1199
01:43:37,550 --> 01:43:38,699
Now, Jim...

1200
01:43:39,070 --> 01:43:40,344
...stand up.

1201
01:43:41,950 --> 01:43:43,702
I'll stand up with you.

1202
01:43:44,230 --> 01:43:47,859
I'll try and be as strong
as you want me to be. Come on.

1203
01:44:18,390 --> 01:44:22,303
This poor baby got nobody. Just nobody!

1204
01:44:50,550 --> 01:44:52,461
He was always cold.

1205
01:45:10,190 --> 01:45:11,623
This is Judy.

1206
01:45:12,190 --> 01:45:13,305
She's my friend.

1207
01:45:32,590 --> 01:45:33,864
He's...

